  "name": "Hobble Mount",
  "desc": "When you cast **hobble mount** as a successful melee spell attack against a horse, wolf, or other four-legged or two-legged beast being ridden as a mount, that beast is disabled so that it can’t move at its normal speed without incurring injury. An affected creature that moves more than half its base speed in a turn takes 2d6 bludgeoning damage.\n\nThis spell has no effect on a creature that your GM deems to not be a mount.\n",
